@startuml
title Workload Distribution Architecture - Structure

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F7F9FC
  BorderColor #4A6FA5
}

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as Consumers

cloud "Cloud Environment" as Cloud {

  rectangle "Load Balancer" as LB

  package "Virtual Server A" as VSA {
    component "Cloud Service A" as CSA1
  }

  package "Virtual Server B" as VSB {
    component "Cloud Service A\n(redundant copy)" as CSA2
  }

  package "Supporting Mechanisms" as Mechs {
    component "Audit Monitor" as AM
    component "Cloud Usage Monitor" as CUM
    component "Hypervisor" as HV
    component "Logical Network\nPerimeter" as LNP
    component "Resource Cluster\n(active-active)" as RC
    component "Resource Replication" as RR
  }
}

Consumers -right-> LB : requests
LB --> CSA1 : even distribution
LB --> CSA2 : even distribution

HV ..> VSA : hosts
HV ..> VSB : hosts
RR ..> CSA2 : generates\ninstances
LNP ..> Cloud : isolates
AM ..> LB : legal/regulatory\nmonitoring
CUM ..> LB : workload tracking
RC ..> VSA : cluster node
RC ..> VSB : cluster node

note bottom of Mechs
  Mechanisms beyond the base load balancer,
  virtual server, and cloud storage device.
end note

@enduml
